  "name": "Blue Dragon's Breath Potion (Young)",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This liquid contains blood from a blue dragon. For 1 hour after you imbibe the concoction, you can unleash a blue dragon's breath weapon. The potency of the breath depends on the potion's type, based on the age of the dragon whose blood was used to make the potion.</p>\n<p>Exhaling dragon breath uses a single action. You create a @Template[type:line|distance:30] of electricity which deals @Damage[4d6[electricity]] damage. All creatures in the area must attempt a @Check[type:reflex|dc:23|basic:true|name:Young Blue Dragon's Breath Potion] save.</p>\n<p>After you use the breath weapon, you can't do so again for [[/r 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>"
